-- Probe: effects written by BARE assert after a decl-only membership
-- (`effects ∈ Seq(Effect)` then `effects = ⟨a⟩`) — p59 showed the
-- membership-pin name-element writer puts effects into state-fields
-- (kernel: stuck). Does the bare-assert writer avoid that?

import "stdlib/kernel.ev"

claim main
    a ∈ Effect = Exit(0)
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect)
    effects = ⟨a⟩
    sentinel ∈ Int = 42
